pull.title: qt: define QT_NO_KEYWORDS
pull.body:
QT_NO_KEYWORDS prevents Qt from defining the `foreach`, `signals`, `slots` and `emit` macros.

Avoid overlap between Qt macros and boost - for example #undef hackiness in #6421.

The drawback is that all uses of the macros have to be replace by Q_xxx, but  at least this is easy to review.

Cc: @sipa @theuni

repo.name: bitcoin
repo.description: Laanwj's Bitcoin Core fork - see README.md on "readme" branch

events.body: Quick glance utACK. Nice fix. IMO it's more readable this way anyway, since it makes it more obvious to the casual reader that signals/slots are just sugary macros and not some c++ functionality they're not aware of.
